      <bioghist id="aspace_f0f2626e4fcd82ffcf575079be342524">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Council of Masters was established in 1932, the year the first masters were appointed. The Council makes recommendations to the University President in matters of policy concerning the residential colleges. It also serves as the committee of control in the affairs concerning two or more residential colleges. The Council consists of the masters of the residential colleges. Ex officio members include the University President, Provost Dean of Yale College, Associate Dean of Yale College and Associate Dean for Student Affairs.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_819d05167d178d4b9baa0ce1d21618ee">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of minutes and associated files of the monthly Yale Council of Masters meetings.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_7919bf39b397ed8eaaede4f914ad355d">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The title "Master" for chief executive officers of residential colleges was changed to "Head of College" in April of 2016.</p>  
      </bioghist>
