            <did>
               <unittitle>Council of Masters meeting minutes</unittitle>
               <unitid>Series I</unitid>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_abd561ec6cc46601d7fc5b4296fedf69">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The records contain minutes and material related to the monthly Council of Masters meetings, 1932-2005. Most records from 1932-1992 include associated meeting files, but records from 1993-2005 contain only minutes and the semiannual student census summaries. Associated files may include votes and agreements, memoranda, correspondence with Yale and New Haven administrators, meeting agendas, and requests for Fellows appointments.</p>
               <p>The main content of the minutes themselves concerns the naming and allocation of Fellows to the residential colleges. Other matters mentioned in the minutes include the residential college libraries; visiting hours for women (pre-1969); the coat and tie rule in dining halls; policies for students returning from war; and distribution of Council of Masters funds to student organizations.</p>
               <p>Indices to the meeting minutes for the years 1935-1965 can be found in Box 1. The bound volumes for the years 1932-1943 also contain indices.</p>
            </scopecontent>
